whereas.text:
Whereas the maritime domain of the Asia-Pacific region
			 includes critical sea lines of communication and commerce between the Pacific
			 and Indian oceans;

Whereas the United States has a national interest in
			 freedom of navigation and overflight in the Asia-Pacific maritime domains, as
			 provided for by universally recognized principles of international law;

Whereas the South China Sea contains great natural
			 resources, and their stewardship and responsible use offers immense potential
			 benefit for generations to come;
